article.description: — Dakota Leffew's 20 points helped Mount St. Mary's defeat Loyola (Maryland) 77-64 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Leffew scores 20, Mount St. Mary's knocks off Loyola (MD) 77-64
article.linkText: Leffew scores 20, Mount St. Mary's knocks off Loyola (MD) 77-64
article.story: BALTIMORE -- — Dakota Leffew's 20 points helped Mount St. Mary's defeat Loyola (Maryland) 77-64 on Saturday night. Leffew had five rebounds, five assists, and three steals for the Mountaineers (3-6). Dallas Hobbs was 5 of 7 shooting and 8 of 9 from the free throw line to add 20 points. Jedy Cordilia had 10 points and shot 5 of 7 from the field. D'Angelo Stines led the way for the Greyhounds (1-9) with 12 points. Alonso Faure added nine points for Loyola. Deon Perry also had nine points. The Greyhounds extended their losing streak to eight straight. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
